                "fragments": [],
                "text": "The renormalization group technique is used to study rigorously the \u03bb(\u2207\u03c6)4 perturbation of the massless lattice field \u03c6 in dimensionsd\u22672. Asymptoticity of the perturbation expansion in powers of \u03bb is established for the free energy density. This is achieved by using Kadanoff's block spin transformation successively to integrate out high momentum degrees of freedom and by applying ideas previously used by Gallavotti and Balaban in the context of the ultraviolet problems. The method works for arbitrary semibounded polynomials in \u2207\u03c6 and \u25b3\u03c6."
